headline.main: Space Artifacts of Soviets Soar at a $7 Million Auction

results.snippet: In what may have been history's most audacious sale of a used vehicle, Sotheby's yesterday auctioned off a research vehicle the Russians left on the surface of the moon in 1970. The price was $68,500.   "We made sure we didn't promise to deliver...
results.lead_paragraph: In what may have been history's most audacious sale of a used vehicle, Sotheby's yesterday auctioned off a research vehicle the Russians left on the surface of the moon in 1970. The price was $68,500. "We made sure we didn't promise to deliver it," said David N. Redden, the senior vice president of the auction house who organized the sale over a three-year period.
